-- Lloyds Said to Plan Sale of U.K. Credit Card-Backed Bonds
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-03-13T12:18:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/lloyds-said-to-plan-sale-of-u-k-credit-card-backed-bonds.html
Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  plans to
sell bonds backed by U.K. credit cards, according to a banker
involved in the transaction.  A roadshow for the securities to be issued through Penarth
Series 2012-1 will start March 19, the banker said. Lloyds Bank
is sole arranger of the transaction, while Bank of America Corp.
and Morgan Stanley are lead managers with Lloyds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
 eduarterubia@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
